orumenos, papers on women of the demimonde in Truculentus and Eunuchus, Cistellaria and Poenulus. The second part deals with rhetoric, including the subject of imitation as a stylistic feature, the study of performance comparing oratory and comedy and of declamation. Papers on Ovid's Fasti include a study of failed rape-scenes and papers concerned with women's cults. The last part (Senecan tragedy, Lucan, Statius) focuses on Lucan's Civil War and his treatment of Caesar as well as Statius' Thebaid and Achilleid.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aFrauen. 4aLateinische Literatur. 4aRezeption. 4aRömische Komödie. 4aRömische Rhetorik. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh  aLatin Literature.  aRoman comedy.  aRoman rhetoric.  aWomen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2010z9783110233575oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311022933240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022934940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110229349423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110229349/original  a978-3-11-023355-1  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010b2010  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSH